    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - Fuel System - Cleaning and Inspection
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s26512.2">
        <title>Cleaning and Inspection</title>
        <svcproc id="m7" svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields. Limit compressed
                        air pressure to 207 kPa (30 psi).
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect fuel lines for kinks, chaffing or other signs of damage. Replace fuel lines if
                    necessary.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3001309" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj11/j11060.cgm" type="cgm" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Fuel pressure regulator poppet assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil filter assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Secondary fuel filter housing</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M6 x 25 screw (3)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Pressure regulator cover gasket</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Viton O-ring, size #115</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Poppet gasket seal</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Brass poppet</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Pressure regulator valve spring</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check poppet valve and spring for signs of misalignment. Inspect poppet gasket seal for
                    signs of uneven seating with the fuel filter housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_198.xml" xrefid="f3900007221">fuel return tube assembly</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="f3900007221"/>
                    for broken or cracked pieces.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean out any accumulated sediment in the bottom of the secondary fuel filter housing
                    and HFCM housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Wash all fuel filter components in a suitable solvent and dry with filtered compressed
                    air.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>See EGES-395 Diagnostic Manual for further inspection and repair of fuel system components.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
